<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870929-0018 </DOCNO><HL> Bid of $128 MillionFor EntertainmentPublications Expected</HL><DD> 09/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EPUB GEPUBLISHING (PUB)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> BIRMINGHAM, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Entertainment Publications Inc. said it expects a group -- including members of management and Kidder, Peabody andamp; Co. -- to propose a leveraged buy-out of the company at $26 a share in cash.    A spokesman said the total value of the buy-out would be about $128 million plus expenses. The publisher of discount-coupon books has been told the bid will be made tomorrow when a board meeting is scheduled. The company added &quot;there could be no assurance&quot; a proposal will be made or that, if it is made, it will be accepted.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Entertainment Publications, closed at $25 a share, up $2.75 It has about 4.8 million shares outstanding.    The buy-out group includes H.L. Potiker, president, and S.M. Potiker, executive vice president. The Potikers, husband and wife, hold about 42% of the company's stock, the spokesman said.    In a leveraged buy-out, a small group of investors acquires a company in a transaction financed largely with borrowing. Ultimately the debt is paid with funds generated by the acquired company's operations or the sale of its assets. </TEXT></DOC>